    <updated>2016-01-19T10:03:49.000Z</updated>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>While building <a href="https://zammu.in/" target="_blank" rel="external">Zammu</a>, I had to build some banner images to use for the <a href="https://facebook.com/zammuhq" target="_blank" rel="external">Facebook</a> and <a href="https://twitter.com/zammuhq" target="_blank" rel="external">Twitter</a> cover photos. I am not very good with image editors like <a href="https://www.gimp.org/" target="_blank" rel="external">Gimp</a>. However, I know my way around HTML. These days, you can create any kind of layout with HTML. I just create the HTML needed for my banner image using the awesome <a href="http://getbootstrap.com" target="_blank" rel="external">bootstrap framework</a>. Opened it in Firefox and used the Firefox’s new <a href="https://hacks.mozilla.org/2015/09/trainspotting-firefox-41/" target="_blank" rel="external">“Screenshot Node”</a> feature to grab a snapshot of the image.</p>
<p>Here is a screenshot of me capturing a screenshot :)</p>
<img src="/2016/01/19/creating-banner-images-using-html/banner-image-screenshot.png" alt="Banner Image Screenshot" title="Banner Image Screenshot">
<p>And here is my banner image :)</p>
<img src="/2016/01/19/creating-banner-images-using-html/banner.png" alt="Banner Image" title="Banner Image">
]]></content>
